-- Santander Said to Sell Three-Year Covered Bonds in Euros
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n   a n d   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-02-01T09:39:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/santander-said-to-sell-three-year-covered-bonds-in-euros.html
Banco Santander SA (SAN)  is selling three-
year covered bonds in euros, according to three people with
knowledge of the sale.  The bonds may be priced to yield about 230 basis points
more than the benchmark mid-swap rate, the people said.  Barclays
Capital , Citigroup Inc. and Natixis are managing the deal with
Santander, the people said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  